description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit enthusiastic and motivated Healthcare Assistants to join our expanding, Rapid Response team in Derby City working within the Out of Hours service .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working hours for the service are from 17.30 til 22.00, every day on a shift rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates being based at London Road Community Hospital.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This role will require you travelling across Derby City part of a wider integrated team providing holistic care to patients in their own homes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;It is expected you will have experience working in either a health or social care setting, with clinical skills relevant to the post. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A good standard of English is required, along with good communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a clinical employee it will be your responsibility to ensure that your behaviour and values reflect those set out in the DCHS Way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
